WEBVTT

00:02.736 --> 00:04.072
Right, extra time for tests,

00:04.105 --> 00:05.673
consultation with
a college counselor

00:05.706 --> 00:07.375
with disability experience.

00:07.408 --> 00:08.742
Any other requests
for your big meeting?

00:08.776 --> 00:12.012
"Nah. It's your thing.
You got this, Moms."

00:12.046 --> 00:13.514
Moms. Is that you or him?

00:13.547 --> 00:15.283
Me. But you had to ask.
He's getting cooler.

00:15.316 --> 00:17.885
Well, that's it, then.
Our very last IEP.

00:17.918 --> 00:20.654
Would you like to mark the
occasion in any way at all?

00:20.688 --> 00:22.256
Would you? No.

00:22.290 --> 00:23.624
All right, well, you're gonna
hate this, then.

00:23.657 --> 00:24.825
* Y'all ready for this

00:24.858 --> 00:29.763
Let's get ready for
JJ's final IEP ever!

00:29.797 --> 00:31.932
The last chance for
your mother to fight

00:31.965 --> 00:33.767
for all the services you need

00:33.801 --> 00:36.537
to make this last
school year awesome.

00:36.570 --> 00:38.005
Awesome. Awesome.

00:38.038 --> 00:39.840
Hey, JJ, I was skeptical,

00:39.873 --> 00:42.643
but I'm a sucker for merch.
[ Laughs ]

00:42.676 --> 00:45.379
And now, at 5'10 and an age

00:45.413 --> 00:47.548
she won't even disclose
to her husband,

00:47.581 --> 00:53.221
give it up for the hero of
the IEP, Maya DiMeo!!

00:53.254 --> 00:54.722
Yeah.

00:54.755 --> 00:55.989
Whoo!

00:56.023 --> 00:59.727
Whoo-hoo! Whoo! Whoo! Whoo!

00:59.760 --> 01:01.028
Jimmy: And it's time for Dylan.
Maya: Dylan!

01:01.061 --> 01:03.063
All: Go, Dylan! Go, Dylan!

01:03.097 --> 01:06.066
Go, Dylan! Go, Dylan! Go, Dylan!

01:06.100 --> 01:10.304
Go, Dylan! Go, Dylan!
Go, Dylan! Go, Dylan!

01:10.338 --> 01:13.207
Go, Dylan! Go, Dylan!
Are we ready to do it?

01:13.241 --> 01:15.943
Wait, if you're Dylan,
who's the bear?

01:18.712 --> 01:21.849
[ Door opens, closes ]

01:21.882 --> 01:23.917
Was it the guy who brought
the balloons?

01:23.951 --> 01:26.920
-- Captions by VITAC --

01:26.954 --> 01:29.923
**

01:29.957 --> 01:32.760
JJ, what is with you
and this jacket?

01:32.793 --> 01:33.961
It's a weird color.

01:33.994 --> 01:35.363
Zippers give you trouble.

01:35.396 --> 01:36.564
"Somebody said" --

01:36.597 --> 01:38.499
Yeah, yeah, somebody said
that you looked like

01:38.532 --> 01:40.268
Pat Sajak in it once.

01:40.301 --> 01:42.203
But since when is that the bar?

01:42.236 --> 01:43.771
Let's lose it.

01:43.804 --> 01:45.439
"Zip it."

01:46.440 --> 01:48.942
Sorry.
I can't be part of this.

01:51.479 --> 01:59.220
**

01:59.253 --> 02:07.060
**

02:07.094 --> 02:08.596
W-- dude, you did it!

02:08.629 --> 02:10.164
I thought you couldn't
do zippers.

02:10.198 --> 02:11.599
"So did I.

02:11.632 --> 02:14.602
Someone said I couldn't
when I was six

02:14.635 --> 02:16.570
and I never tried since.

02:16.604 --> 02:18.772
Wonder what else I can do."

02:18.806 --> 02:20.241
Well, let's find out!

02:20.274 --> 02:22.376
Let's do some stuff
no one thinks you can!

02:22.410 --> 02:23.711
[ School bell rings ]

02:23.744 --> 02:26.680
Wait,
you tried talking, right?

02:28.182 --> 02:31.084
Dylan, we're gonna go see
Devon's band tonight at 9:00.

02:31.118 --> 02:32.286
You in?
9:00?

02:32.320 --> 02:35.456
No, thanks.
I'll be making Z's.

02:35.489 --> 02:36.624
What time do you
go to bed?

02:36.657 --> 02:37.691
Well, my bedtime is 8:00,

02:37.725 --> 02:40.461
but I get screen time
in bed till 8:15.

02:40.494 --> 02:41.895
Perks of being
in high school.

02:41.929 --> 02:44.232
You got bed at 8:00
every night?

02:44.265 --> 02:45.899
Yeah,
my parents always say,

02:45.933 --> 02:49.069
"10 hours of sleep is what
a growing girl needs."

02:49.102 --> 02:50.738
Yeah, my whole family
goes to bed early.

02:50.771 --> 02:51.939
Okay...

02:51.972 --> 02:52.973
What?

02:53.006 --> 02:55.576
Ray, is my bedtime
super early?

02:55.609 --> 02:58.812
"10 hours of sleep is what
a growing girl needs."

02:58.846 --> 03:03.284
**

03:03.317 --> 03:04.985
All right, let's do this.
Whoa, whoa.

03:05.018 --> 03:06.887
Don't you know the pre-drive
safety checklist?

03:06.920 --> 03:09.022
I'm sorry. I didn't have
a lot of time to study.

03:09.056 --> 03:10.658
Junior year,
you know how it is --

03:10.691 --> 03:12.993
SATs,
researching colleges.

03:13.026 --> 03:14.962
Look, kid, I wear a lot of hats
at this school.

03:14.995 --> 03:15.863
Low-stakes stuff.

03:15.896 --> 03:17.164
I teach some Spanish wrong,

03:17.197 --> 03:19.066
they don't know donde
the biblioteca is.

03:19.099 --> 03:20.301
The world keeps spinning.

03:20.334 --> 03:23.337
If you blow off drivers ed,
people die!

03:23.371 --> 03:25.172
If you can't handle the duties
of a high school junior

03:25.205 --> 03:26.774
without committing
vehicular manslaughter,

03:26.807 --> 03:28.141
get out of this car!

03:28.175 --> 03:32.012
**

03:32.045 --> 03:34.382
Now, I'm sure it's not
lost on any of you

03:34.415 --> 03:36.784
that this is our last IEP.

03:36.817 --> 03:40.120
And what a wonderful journey
we've shared together.

03:40.153 --> 03:41.922
You know, that being said,

03:41.955 --> 03:44.725
I will haunt you to your graves
if I don't get exactly what I--

03:44.758 --> 03:46.594
Maya.
Sorry to interrupt,

03:46.627 --> 03:49.630
but um, JJ's been on
a self-empowerment kick.

03:49.663 --> 03:51.699
Do you mind if, uh,
he makes some requests?

03:51.732 --> 03:53.934
Oh, no! No, not at all.
That's wonderful, darling.

03:53.967 --> 03:55.102
Go on.

03:55.135 --> 03:56.203
Uh, "number one,

03:56.236 --> 03:58.706
I'd like unlimited time
for tests,

03:58.739 --> 04:00.173
instead of time
and a half."

04:00.207 --> 04:03.544
"Number two, I'd like to take
tests in a private space."

04:03.577 --> 04:05.045
Oh,
I didn't think of that.

04:05.078 --> 04:06.714
You know, I was also
thinking, if we --

04:06.747 --> 04:08.382
"Number three..."

04:08.416 --> 04:10.318
And "36,

04:10.351 --> 04:13.086
scheduling flexibility to
accommodate attendance

04:13.120 --> 04:15.088
of college
community classes."

04:15.122 --> 04:17.558
Goodness, JJ, such initiative.

04:17.591 --> 04:21.028
It is with great pride that
I say to all your requests,

04:21.061 --> 04:22.463
"We will look into them."

04:22.496 --> 04:24.965
When did you become
so ambitious, darling?

04:24.998 --> 04:27.134
"I zipped my zipper today."

04:27.167 --> 04:29.437
What?
But you can't zip your zipper.

04:29.470 --> 04:31.705
"Turns out I can.

04:31.739 --> 04:34.241
I can do a lot of things

04:34.274 --> 04:37.711
I thought people
had to do for me."

04:37.745 --> 04:39.480
**

04:39.513 --> 04:41.815
Oh, uh,
do my zipper for 'em.

04:41.849 --> 04:44.885
[ Laughs ]

04:49.523 --> 04:51.224
Okay, this was a bad idea.

04:51.258 --> 04:53.894
And then he ran the meeting
all by himself.

04:53.927 --> 04:55.228
Well, that's great, right?

04:55.262 --> 04:57.898
Of course. I've always wanted JJ
to take care of himself.

04:57.931 --> 05:01.068
But standing there listening
to him do what I've done

05:01.101 --> 05:03.236
all these years, well,
if he takes care of JJ,

05:03.270 --> 05:04.271
then what do I do?

05:04.304 --> 05:06.540
I got a C
on my English paper!

05:06.574 --> 05:07.941
Junior year's too hard!

05:07.975 --> 05:09.276
I'm gonna fail my classes,

05:09.309 --> 05:11.945
not get into college,
get a job delivering pizzas,

05:11.979 --> 05:13.113
but I failed drivers ed

05:13.146 --> 05:15.383
so I'm gonna kill 50 people
on my first day

05:15.416 --> 05:17.150
and spend the rest of
my life behind bars

05:17.184 --> 05:18.986
making other prisoners my "B"!

05:19.019 --> 05:21.389
You'll make them --
uh-huh.

05:21.422 --> 05:23.223
My life is over!

05:25.693 --> 05:27.495
When God closes a door,

05:27.528 --> 05:29.997
he annihilates one
of our children.

05:30.030 --> 05:32.299
What a day!
I'll be in bed soon, too.

05:32.332 --> 05:33.901
Good night, Princess.
Good night.

05:33.934 --> 05:39.973
**

05:41.875 --> 05:44.177
Night Jenga?
Uh...

05:44.211 --> 05:46.514
So, you all coincidentally
decided

05:46.547 --> 05:48.516
to break your bedtimes
tonight?

05:48.549 --> 05:50.584
Okay, here's the deal.
Three kids are a lot.

05:50.618 --> 05:53.353
Bedtime is a parent's
only reprieve.

05:53.387 --> 05:56.089
JJ and Ray aging out of bedtime
was bad enough.

05:56.123 --> 05:57.791
And when it came time
to give yours up,

05:57.825 --> 06:01.862
we just thought,
"What if we don't?"

06:01.895 --> 06:06.033
And for what it's worth,
we didn't think you'd find out.

06:06.066 --> 06:07.601
You two let this happen?

06:07.635 --> 06:08.702
We like the downtime, too.

06:08.736 --> 06:10.370
"You can be loud."

06:10.404 --> 06:13.373
Well, your wheelchair makes
a low humming noise sometimes.

06:13.407 --> 06:15.275
Look, look,
this is mostly my doing.

06:15.308 --> 06:17.044
I-I need my alone time.

06:17.077 --> 06:18.846
These guys are not up
much later than you.

06:18.879 --> 06:20.514
Then I'm coming for you.

06:20.548 --> 06:23.350
I'm never sleeping again.

06:23.383 --> 06:24.818
You owe me night.

06:24.852 --> 06:26.053
Yeah, I-I --

06:26.086 --> 06:27.988
**

06:28.021 --> 06:31.224
Ohh, how sweet it is.

06:31.258 --> 06:32.926
Yeah.

06:32.960 --> 06:34.662
Oh!

06:34.695 --> 06:36.997
Hey, I-I thought this
was your free period.

06:37.030 --> 06:39.199
"This looks fun.
I want in."

06:39.232 --> 06:40.367
You want to play?

06:40.400 --> 06:43.704
No, you can't be in here
gambling with adults.

06:43.737 --> 06:45.906
"'Can't'?
Who are you, a zipper?"

06:45.939 --> 06:47.841
[ Laughter ]
What are you
laughing at?

06:47.875 --> 06:49.543
You don't even know what
that's referring to.

06:49.577 --> 06:51.545
Uh, it's referring to you,
zipper.

06:51.579 --> 06:52.646
[ Laughter ]

06:53.947 --> 06:55.883
Out of my way, punk!
Ugh, I'm sorry,

06:55.916 --> 06:57.551
I've already given
my lunch money to Corbin.

06:57.585 --> 06:59.052
I got you.
Wait, Mom?

06:59.086 --> 07:01.388
What are you doing here?
Is something wrong with JJ?

07:01.421 --> 07:03.390
No, no, no, no, I just had
a bit more time on my hands.

07:03.423 --> 07:06.727
So, you know, I know how upset
you were about that C.

07:06.760 --> 07:08.729
So I thought I'd come down here
and talk to your jerk teacher.

07:08.762 --> 07:10.731
You talked to my teacher
about my C?

07:10.764 --> 07:12.065
Yeah, it's a B-plus now.

07:12.099 --> 07:13.901
Oh, I'm sorry,
was I overstepping?

07:13.934 --> 07:16.203
No, Mom, that's amazing.
Thank you.

07:16.236 --> 07:18.105
You know, if you need more help,
I'm happy to give it.

07:18.138 --> 07:19.206
No pressure.

07:19.239 --> 07:21.208
I mean, if it's not
too much trouble.

07:21.241 --> 07:23.176
Yeah, 'cause, I mean, I do have
a bit more time now...

07:23.210 --> 07:25.378
Enough games,
I want it all.

07:25.412 --> 07:27.414
Now, where's that Corbin?

07:27.447 --> 07:28.816
I am hugging my mom
in the hallway,

07:28.849 --> 07:31.084
so he should be here
any second.

07:34.021 --> 07:37.858
Please just go to bed.

07:37.891 --> 07:39.727
I promise you're not
missing anything.

07:39.760 --> 07:41.729
That's exactly what
someone who stays up late

07:41.762 --> 07:43.330
doing something awesome
would say.

07:43.363 --> 07:45.899
Actually,

07:45.933 --> 07:49.102
what I like to do
at night is...

07:49.136 --> 07:52.405
read John Steinbeck's classic,
"The Grapes of Wrath".

07:52.439 --> 07:53.674
Out loud.

07:53.707 --> 07:55.743
Your threat relies on me
knowing that book is boring.

07:55.776 --> 07:57.444
And I don't.
[ Sighs ]

07:57.477 --> 07:59.212
Fine.

07:59.246 --> 08:01.048
You want to see what I do?

08:01.081 --> 08:03.717
It's dumb stuff like this.

08:03.751 --> 08:05.418
I don't fight crime.

08:05.452 --> 08:07.588
I don't make inventions.

08:07.621 --> 08:09.857
But we have a lot going on.

08:09.890 --> 08:12.860
And I need to
turn off my brain

08:12.893 --> 08:16.697
and recharge my battery with
dumb stuff that doesn't matter.

08:16.730 --> 08:19.366
Oh, my God, Dad,
you just made five in a row.

08:19.399 --> 08:21.468
Six.

08:21.501 --> 08:22.670
Seven.

08:22.703 --> 08:28.842
**

08:28.876 --> 08:31.845
Eight, nine, ten.
Dad, you're awesome.

08:31.879 --> 08:34.014
Are you the reason
I'm awesome?

08:34.047 --> 08:37.384
Um, your mom's asleep,
so yeah. Yes.

08:37.417 --> 08:39.352
Well, you clearly
use this time.

08:39.386 --> 08:41.154
I don't want to
get in the way.

08:41.188 --> 08:43.523
Maybe someday, you'll show me
the other stuff you can do.

08:43.557 --> 08:46.326
Okay.

08:46.359 --> 08:47.795
Unless...

08:47.828 --> 08:50.163
I can show you right now...

08:50.197 --> 08:53.433
**

08:53.466 --> 08:54.467
Maya: There he is.

08:55.869 --> 08:58.538
"Maya DiMeo presents
Ray's Junior Year."
"Ray's Junior Year."

08:58.572 --> 09:00.207
Yeah.
Study schedules,

09:00.240 --> 09:02.843
college prep, realistic goals
and benchmarks.

09:02.876 --> 09:04.211
And I hope you don't mind,

09:04.244 --> 09:06.479
but I took the liberty
of identifying

09:06.513 --> 09:09.316
a few dating prospects I think
you might have overlooked.

09:09.349 --> 09:11.051
Have you really given
Amy P. a chance?

09:11.084 --> 09:15.055
Mom, this is so overly detailed
and intense.

09:15.088 --> 09:17.357
I love it!
I knew you would.

09:19.492 --> 09:23.196
Right, let's practice the line
I taught you to say to girls.

09:23.230 --> 09:26.199
Now you tell me
your interests.

09:26.233 --> 09:27.500
Very good.

09:27.534 --> 09:30.704
See, I've labeled them
Monday through Friday.

09:30.738 --> 09:33.340
That way, you don't have to
waste any brain space

09:33.373 --> 09:34.708
figuring out what
to wear to school.

09:34.742 --> 09:36.910
I am loving
that Tuesday look.

09:36.944 --> 09:38.578
Me, too!

09:38.612 --> 09:40.113
Oh, hey, guys.

09:40.147 --> 09:41.181
You see Tuesday?

09:41.214 --> 09:43.050
"Mom's help can be nice.

09:43.083 --> 09:44.517
But you need boundaries."

09:44.551 --> 09:47.755
JJ, the only boundary I need
is between me and your jealousy.

09:47.788 --> 09:48.989
Mom's been all about you.

09:49.022 --> 09:50.123
Now it's Ray's turn.

09:50.157 --> 09:52.059
Ray, before we
go to the store,

09:52.092 --> 09:53.426
would you like to
use the bathroom?

09:53.460 --> 09:54.628
You've had
a lot of juice.

09:54.662 --> 09:55.696
I have.

09:55.729 --> 09:57.397
And I shall.

09:57.430 --> 09:58.565
Thank you, Mother.

09:58.598 --> 10:01.201
**

10:01.234 --> 10:03.070
There we go.
Do the honors.

10:04.838 --> 10:06.774
The perfect
paper airplane.

10:06.807 --> 10:08.541
Bet you it stays up there
for five minutes.

10:12.112 --> 10:13.346
You lose.

10:13.380 --> 10:14.447
That was the most
perfect spitball

10:14.481 --> 10:16.249
I've ever seen in my life!

10:16.283 --> 10:17.685
I could, um [yawns]

10:17.718 --> 10:19.386
I could show you
how to do it.

10:19.419 --> 10:21.922
Nah, it's getting late.
You should get to bed.

10:21.955 --> 10:23.423
But you were gonna list
all of the presidents

10:23.456 --> 10:24.391
in order of height.

10:24.424 --> 10:25.893
Number eight might
surprise you.

10:25.926 --> 10:27.194
I'll go put on
another pot.

10:27.227 --> 10:28.896
Whoa. Since when
do you drink coffee?

10:28.929 --> 10:31.899
Since I realized how awesome
you were at night.

10:31.932 --> 10:34.634
10 worst parents
of all time --

10:34.668 --> 10:37.637
number one will not
surprise you.

10:37.671 --> 10:40.808
[ School bell rings ]

10:40.841 --> 10:44.878
"Oh, no, I left my big
history paper at home.

10:44.912 --> 10:46.714
Will you get it?"

10:46.747 --> 10:48.682
Oh, oh, Mr. Powers,
can you do me a favor?

10:48.716 --> 10:52.052
Are you Ellen DeGeneres'
exclusive online content? No?

10:52.085 --> 10:54.387
Then why are you talking to me
during my free period?

10:54.421 --> 10:57.157
Uh, I-I just need you to help JJ
while I go get his paper.

10:57.190 --> 10:59.326
Oh, it's for JJ?
Then, sure!

10:59.359 --> 11:00.527
Be right back.

11:03.630 --> 11:05.665
Oh, people
hang out in here?

11:05.699 --> 11:06.934
Bleak!

11:06.967 --> 11:08.335
JJ, you wanna play?

11:08.368 --> 11:10.303
Uh, "deal me in."

11:10.337 --> 11:12.205
Oh, wait, sorry, now that
I know what you're going for,

11:12.239 --> 11:13.941
let me take that again.
[ Clears throat ]

11:13.974 --> 11:15.843
"Deal me in."

11:15.876 --> 11:20.180
Wait, you play poker in here for
money during your free period?

11:20.213 --> 11:21.648
Oh, I don't know...

11:21.681 --> 11:24.818
"I'm taking charge
of my own life.

11:24.852 --> 11:26.286
I zipped my zipper.

11:26.319 --> 11:28.355
I just need you to help me."

11:28.388 --> 11:30.991
I read for JJ.

11:31.024 --> 11:33.560
He's an even bigger zipper
than your normal guy.

11:34.895 --> 11:36.997
Maya, are you home?

11:37.030 --> 11:39.232
I'm here for JJ's history pap...

11:40.868 --> 11:42.369
Mother's at the grocery.

11:42.402 --> 11:44.437
And I'm taking a day off
to rest.

11:44.471 --> 11:46.239
Mother says, "Mental health

11:46.273 --> 11:49.843
is just as important
as physical health."

11:49.877 --> 11:52.712
I'm just looking for JJ's
history paper, man.

11:57.484 --> 11:59.219
Oh, got it.

12:03.423 --> 12:05.525
[ Elvis Presley's "A Little Less
Conversation" plays ]

12:05.558 --> 12:06.827
Ooh!

12:06.860 --> 12:11.531
**

12:11.564 --> 12:13.033
Boom!

12:13.066 --> 12:17.037
**

12:17.070 --> 12:19.072
You are so good at this!

12:20.273 --> 12:22.642
Now, let's make this
the best possible

12:22.675 --> 12:24.311
drivers ed experience
for my Ray.

12:24.344 --> 12:25.779
What's holding you back?

12:25.813 --> 12:28.048
Well, okay, well,
I'm not big on lefts...

12:28.081 --> 12:31.384
Hmm, "no left turns."
What else?

12:31.418 --> 12:34.021
Uh, I don't really know
what "yield" means?

12:34.054 --> 12:35.188
Forget that one.
Nobody does.

12:35.222 --> 12:36.423
What else?
The driver instructor.

12:36.456 --> 12:37.557
He's tough love.

12:37.590 --> 12:39.459
I find I'm more of
a praise-based learner.

12:39.492 --> 12:40.727
I'll be tackling that
at the meeting.

12:40.760 --> 12:41.995
What meeting?
Dr. Miller,

12:42.029 --> 12:43.797
the driving instructor,
and I will be meeting

12:43.831 --> 12:45.365
to discuss how best to serve

12:45.398 --> 12:47.067
your individual
drivers ed needs.

12:47.100 --> 12:49.937
That sounds a lot like those
IEP things you do for JJ.

12:49.970 --> 12:51.004
I know. Isn't that great?

12:51.038 --> 12:53.406
'Cause I thought I'd done
my last IEP.

12:53.440 --> 12:56.543
"Just when I thought I was
out...they pull me back in!"

12:56.576 --> 12:58.311
Uh...
I feel like it was more,

12:58.345 --> 13:00.613
you were out and they
were okay with that,

13:00.647 --> 13:02.549
and you, uh, you forced
your way back in.

13:02.582 --> 13:03.716
Hoo-wa!

13:03.750 --> 13:11.524
**

13:11.558 --> 13:13.293
I fold.
I fold, too.

13:13.326 --> 13:15.462
Oh, this is intense.

13:15.495 --> 13:17.130
Maybe quit while you're ahead.

13:19.933 --> 13:20.968
Oh...

13:23.470 --> 13:24.771
All of it?

13:27.074 --> 13:29.409
"I won all that, didn't I?"

13:33.713 --> 13:35.648
"I know he's bluffing.

13:35.682 --> 13:39.486
He has a tell.
He's doing it right now."

13:42.890 --> 13:44.892
Okay, enough, JJ!

13:44.925 --> 13:47.194
"I know what I'm doing.

13:47.227 --> 13:49.729
I Z-I-P-- "zipped my zipper."

13:49.762 --> 13:51.865
I don't understand why you keep
bringing that up!

13:51.899 --> 13:53.133
All right,
you're out of cash.

13:53.166 --> 13:55.268
If you want to stay in the game,
what else do you got?

13:55.302 --> 13:58.671
**

14:00.673 --> 14:06.646
**

14:06.679 --> 14:09.816
So...did you win?

14:12.152 --> 14:13.353
Dr. Miller:
Thank you for coming.

14:13.386 --> 14:15.855
How are things
at home, Jimmy?

14:15.889 --> 14:18.191
Well, you know, Dad drinks
more than I'd like,

14:18.225 --> 14:20.860
and Mom's just kind
of checked out --

14:20.894 --> 14:23.230
you mean my current home.
Good! They're good. Good.

14:24.564 --> 14:26.866
I'd like you to take
a look at Dylan.

14:26.900 --> 14:30.337
[ Band playing ]

14:30.370 --> 14:31.504
[ Sighs ]

14:34.341 --> 14:35.909
She looks
kind of tired, huh?

14:35.943 --> 14:38.045
Is there any reason why
she wouldn't

14:38.078 --> 14:39.446
be getting
enough sleep?

14:39.479 --> 14:41.314
I think I know
what this is about.
Mm-hmm.

14:41.348 --> 14:43.850
It won't be easy,
but I can fix it.

14:43.883 --> 14:46.219
I'm a dad.
I make things better.

14:46.253 --> 14:47.487
Oh, good.

14:48.588 --> 14:53.526
**

14:53.560 --> 14:54.694
Yeah,
one thing at a time.

14:54.727 --> 14:56.863
Nothing.
Don't worry about it.

14:56.896 --> 15:00.433
Ray, I've got
a surprise for you...

15:02.569 --> 15:04.204
Ta-da!

15:04.237 --> 15:06.706
I made it for you.

15:06.739 --> 15:10.377
That way, if you need me,
you don't have to get up.

15:10.410 --> 15:13.013
You can just
roll right over.

15:13.046 --> 15:14.781
Isn't this basically
a wheelchair?

15:14.814 --> 15:16.483
Save your voice
for the debate club.

15:16.516 --> 15:20.287
But if you absolutely need
to speak, here's this.

15:20.320 --> 15:22.555
Look at you.
[ Gasps ]

15:22.589 --> 15:24.724
You're perfect, JJ.

15:24.757 --> 15:26.759
I'm Ray! I'm Ray!

15:26.793 --> 15:29.729
**

15:29.762 --> 15:31.764
Aaaah!

15:31.798 --> 15:34.534
Aah!

15:34.567 --> 15:36.869
Oh, thank God.

15:36.903 --> 15:39.572
It was just a terrible,
plausible dream.

15:42.742 --> 15:47.647
**

15:47.680 --> 15:48.715
Where are you going, Ray?

15:48.748 --> 15:50.917
Uh, I should probably
get to school.

15:50.950 --> 15:52.585
I think I can make
my last class.

15:52.619 --> 15:53.987
But not drivers ed, right?

15:54.021 --> 15:56.289
Because we still have to
discuss your special needs --

15:56.323 --> 15:57.324
I mean, your needs.
I don't think we need

15:57.357 --> 15:58.558
to have that meeting.

15:58.591 --> 15:59.792
I mean,
it has been great.

15:59.826 --> 16:01.528
"Has been"?
What a ridiculous tense to use

16:01.561 --> 16:03.096
for a clearly
ongoing situation.

16:03.130 --> 16:05.065
Unless you want
me to stop --
No, no, I just --

16:05.098 --> 16:07.300
I just don't want to feel
like I'm hogging you.

16:07.334 --> 16:09.236
You know, there's other people
that need you

16:09.269 --> 16:11.771
like Dylan and --
and Pepper...

16:11.804 --> 16:13.506
and...I should really go.

16:13.540 --> 16:15.708
[ Door opens, closes ]
Ray...

16:15.742 --> 16:18.311
How could you let him
take your chair?

16:18.345 --> 16:21.814
"He won it fair and square."

16:21.848 --> 16:24.884
Why did that dumb game
matter to you so much?

16:24.917 --> 16:28.355
"I want to do things by myself."

16:28.388 --> 16:30.657
You've been doing
tons by yourself.

16:30.690 --> 16:32.259
The IEP, the zipper.

16:32.292 --> 16:34.761
Plus, you really made "zipper"
happen as an insult.

16:34.794 --> 16:36.696
But it can't all happen at once.

16:36.729 --> 16:38.598
You gotta be patient.

16:38.631 --> 16:42.001
"All I've ever been is patient."

16:44.537 --> 16:46.673
JJ, I get it.

16:46.706 --> 16:49.242
But listen, man,
here's the good news --

16:49.276 --> 16:52.379
what you did today

16:52.412 --> 16:54.847
is just because
you're stupid.

16:54.881 --> 16:59.252
Yeah, it had nothing to
do with any disability.

16:59.286 --> 17:01.921
You just didn't know
when to stop.

17:03.223 --> 17:05.725
You're moving. Fast.

17:05.758 --> 17:08.628
But we all need to
know our limits.

17:08.661 --> 17:11.564
"Can you help me
get my chair back?"

17:12.565 --> 17:13.833
Yeah.

17:13.866 --> 17:16.069
I can do business
with the janitor.

17:17.070 --> 17:18.238
I know his price.

17:19.606 --> 17:21.341
[ Yawning ]
Man, what is with me?

17:21.374 --> 17:22.842
Yeah, let Daddy
top you off.

17:22.875 --> 17:24.477
I-I've had,
like, a gallon.

17:24.511 --> 17:26.613
It's -- It's not
doing anything.

17:26.646 --> 17:28.481
Well, maybe it's your body's
way of telling you

17:28.515 --> 17:31.218
that this late-night thing
has run its course.

17:31.251 --> 17:32.485
But I love it --

17:32.519 --> 17:33.920
us doing stupid stuff,

17:33.953 --> 17:36.456
no distractions,
no responsibilities.

17:37.524 --> 17:40.193
I have a pretty big
responsibility.

17:40.227 --> 17:41.461
Oh, come on, Jimbo.

17:41.494 --> 17:44.697
I mean, you've been the one
giving me all the coffee.

17:44.731 --> 17:46.699
Wait! Is this decaf?

17:46.733 --> 17:48.034
How could you?

17:48.067 --> 17:49.469
You gave me no choice.

17:49.502 --> 17:52.505
It turns out, a growing girl
really does need her sleep.

17:52.539 --> 17:55.508
And you know, maybe when
you're done growing,

17:55.542 --> 18:00.180
you and I will be...

18:00.213 --> 18:01.681
the king and queen
of the night.

18:01.714 --> 18:03.916
You do magic, too?!

18:03.950 --> 18:05.318
Go to bed, sweetheart.

18:05.352 --> 18:06.386
No. No.

18:06.419 --> 18:10.490
I'll just rest my eyes
for, like, a minute.

18:10.523 --> 18:12.225
And then [yawns]

18:12.259 --> 18:14.561
I'll be good to go...

18:14.594 --> 18:23.270
**

18:23.303 --> 18:25.405
You're pretty magic yourself.

18:25.438 --> 18:31.378
**

18:31.411 --> 18:37.250
**

18:37.284 --> 18:38.551
[ Horns honk ]

18:38.585 --> 18:40.052
Woman:
Hey, watch it!

18:40.086 --> 18:41.888
Man: Look out!

18:41.921 --> 18:43.690
Take the next right.

18:43.723 --> 18:45.725
You got this, Ray.

18:45.758 --> 18:48.428
[ Horn honks ]

18:48.461 --> 18:51.063
Ray!
You're doing wonderfully!

18:51.097 --> 18:52.765
Mom! Why are you here?!

18:52.799 --> 18:55.435
To give you the positive
reinforcement you require

18:55.468 --> 18:57.204
and this healthful smoothie.

18:57.237 --> 18:59.206
Oh.
Could you just --

18:59.239 --> 19:00.240
Ooh, bugger!

19:00.273 --> 19:02.742
[ Tires screech ]

19:02.775 --> 19:05.378
Ray! That smoothie
looked delicious!

19:05.412 --> 19:06.979
I need to get away
from my mom!

19:07.013 --> 19:11.050
Hey!
A left! Bravo, darling!

19:11.083 --> 19:13.453
Oi, compliment him.
It's how he learns.

19:13.486 --> 19:15.622
Right. Yeah, uh, uh,
g-good job, Ray.

19:15.655 --> 19:18.358
Way to, uh, close your eyes
every time you turn.

19:18.391 --> 19:19.292
[ Tires squeal ]

19:19.326 --> 19:21.794
We're gonna die!
Oh, relax!

19:21.828 --> 19:23.630
Amanda, if we don't
make it out of this alive,

19:23.663 --> 19:25.064
I want you to know
that I love you.

19:25.097 --> 19:26.266
I love you, too.

19:26.299 --> 19:29.035
Hey, I thought we kinda
had a thing happening?

19:29.068 --> 19:30.603
Sorry, no.
Oh, definitely not.

19:30.637 --> 19:32.939
[ Horn honks ]
You did great, love!

19:32.972 --> 19:37.244
**

19:37.277 --> 19:38.345
Ray, stop!

19:40.046 --> 19:41.047
Oh!

19:44.984 --> 19:47.854
Well, you --
that was pretty good.

19:47.887 --> 19:49.356
Leave me alone, Mom!

19:49.389 --> 19:50.957
I can't be your new JJ.

19:50.990 --> 19:53.560
You have to find
something else.

19:53.593 --> 19:56.229
Way to go, Ray.
You failed great!

19:57.730 --> 20:03.102
**

20:03.135 --> 20:06.406
Oh, hey, I missed you.

20:06.439 --> 20:10.543
"Not so easy to
replace me, is it?"

20:10.577 --> 20:12.379
No.

20:12.412 --> 20:14.547
Darling,
I'm so proud of you.

20:14.581 --> 20:17.650
The way you've taken control
of your life.

20:17.684 --> 20:19.719
Your future is so bright.

20:19.752 --> 20:21.354
But when I think
about my future,

20:21.388 --> 20:24.757
I have no idea what my life
looks like with less of you.

20:25.858 --> 20:30.530
"I know how you'd
H-E-- help me."

20:32.565 --> 20:34.033
[ Wheelchair beeps ]

20:34.066 --> 20:37.370
Let's get ready
for Mom's first IEP.

20:38.571 --> 20:43.976
"How can we make this next year
the best year yet?"

20:44.010 --> 20:45.878
That's so sweet of you.

20:45.912 --> 20:47.246
Well?

20:48.748 --> 20:52.251
I'd just really like to know
who was in the bear costume.

20:58.758 --> 21:01.728
Six months of this.
[ Scoffs ]

21:01.761 --> 21:05.031
That janitor is a shrewd
negotiator.

21:05.064 --> 21:06.933
"It's worth it."

21:06.966 --> 21:09.035
Hm. You know what else
could be worth it?

21:09.068 --> 21:10.570
Poker lessons.

21:11.904 --> 21:14.006
Hey. Wha--?

21:14.040 --> 21:19.245
"Wow, I never knew
I could do that."

21:19.278 --> 21:22.181
[ Snorts ] Nice try.

21:22.214 --> 21:23.650
[ Laughs ]
